genresAdvancedInfo.name: dutch experimental
genresAdvancedInfo.description: This genre is characterized by its unconventional and avant-garde approach to music-making. It often incorporates unusual sounds, structures, and instrumentation, and seeks to push the boundaries of what is considered "normal" in music. Dutch experimental music can be challenging to listen to, but it can also be incredibly rewarding for those who are open to its unique and innovative qualities.
